1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,160
A pure function always returns the same output for the same input.

2
00:00:07,160 --> 00:00:10,120
It doesn't change anything outside itself.

3
00:00:10,120 --> 00:00:13,040
React is designed around this idea.

4
00:00:13,040 --> 00:00:17,480
Every component should be a pure function of its props and state.

5
00:00:17,480 --> 00:00:19,880
Pure components are predictable.

6
00:00:19,880 --> 00:00:24,320
Given the same inputs, they always render the same JSX.

7
00:00:24,320 --> 00:00:27,000
In pure components have side effects.

8
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:32,360
They change variables outside their scope, make network calls during render, or modify

9
00:00:32,360 --> 00:00:34,800
the DOM directly.

10
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:39,120
React renders components twice in development strict mode.

11
00:00:39,120 --> 00:00:44,080
This catches impure components that produce different output on each call.

12
00:00:44,080 --> 00:00:48,840
Here's the rule, don't mutate anything that existed before the render started.

13
00:00:48,840 --> 00:00:52,400
Props, state, and context are read only.

14
00:00:52,400 --> 00:00:58,120
You can create and mutate variables inside the component during render, that's fine.

15
00:00:58,120 --> 00:01:00,680
They didn't exist before the call.

16
00:01:00,680 --> 00:01:04,320
Side effects belong in event handlers, not in render.

17
00:01:04,320 --> 00:01:09,000
User clicks, form submissions, timers, those are the right places.

18
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:13,440
If no event handler fits, use use effect as a last resort.

19
00:01:13,440 --> 00:01:17,600
It runs after render outside the pure rendering phase.

20
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:24,440
Pure components unlock two react superpowers, memorization, and concurrent rendering.

21
00:01:24,440 --> 00:01:30,160
Memoization means react can skip re-rendering a component if its inputs haven't changed.

22
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:33,720
This only works if the component is pure.

23
00:01:33,720 --> 00:01:38,760
Concurrent rendering means react can pause, restart, or abandon renders.

24
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:41,600
In pure components break this entirely.

25
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:47,240
The mental model, react components are like math functions, f of x always equals the

26
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:49,840
same result, no surprises.

27
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:57,160
Let's recap, components must be pure, same input, same output, no mutations during render.

28
00:01:57,160 --> 00:02:00,720
Side effects go in event handlers or use effect.

29
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:05,320
That's the react series, one concept at a time from the actual docs.

